The paper discusses a hierarchical approach for modular robots that involves training a neural network to select appropriate motor primitives and robot configurations to achieve a target. This involves elements of robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), control systems (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV) as the robots are trained to recognize and achieve different targets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, and cs.CV.
